.START 

Joseph K. Taussig, 44 years old, was named to the new post of vice chairman of this news and information company.
He remains executive vice president of the information and news group of New York-based Infotechnology Inc., which manages UPI and has an option to buy the company.
Earlier this month, general managers of UPI's new "product line-centered business units" were appointed.
They will report to Mr. Taussig, who will concentrate on administering the cooperation of the businesses, which include sports, international, finance and pictures. 

